 POLICE have released a photo of a man who was found dead in a flat. 
 The body of Latvian Aleksandrs Sokolovs, 29, was discovered in a property in Tummel Road, Glenrothes in Fife, on Monday. 
The death is being treated as suspicious and officers say they are following a positive line of inquiry.
A 28-year-old man has been arrested over a matter in connection with the police investigation.
